'''Acheron''' is an inhospitably cold landmass somewhere north of the [[Fremennik Province]] and the islands of the [[Lunar Sea]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Brundt the Chieftain|quote=North of this town the atmosphere becomes bitterly cold. There are a number of small inhabited islands that we have sea routes with... ...Beyond those islands, there is a large frozen wasteland we call Acheron.}} It is described as a terribly vicious place where no living thing should survive,{{CitePostbag|issue=20|author=[[Brundt the Chieftain|Chieftain Brundt]]|letter=4|quote=the frozen lands of Acheron are a terrible vicious place. We do not fear the cold but there are things up there that live where no living thing should survive. The stories tell of icy winds with intent so malicious they will wrap themselves around your heart until it freezes like stone|name=Postbag}} those who would venture into the perilous environment require an agile and sturdy body to survive.{{CiteNPC|npc=Brundt the Chieftain|quote=It is an inhospitable land, and you will need an agile and sturdy body just to keep alive in it's perils.}} The [[Fremennik]] share stories of icy winds on Acheron that could freeze hearts to stone{{NamedRef|Postbag}} and the crew of the [[Lady Zay]] jokingly state Acheron is cold enough to freeze spoken words.{{CiteNPC|npc='Lecherous' Lee|loc=Lady Zay|quote=Up by Acheron it gets so cold that when you talk you see the words freeze in the air in front of you!}}

[[Brundt the Chieftain]] states that the Fremennik will lead an expedition to Acheron after the [[Dagannoth|daggermouth]] threat is dealt with.{{CitePostbag|issue=20|author=[[Brundt the Chieftain|Chieftain Brundt]]|letter=4|quote=In good time we will venture north and warm the very winds themselves with our battle cries and song; unlike the scurvy pirates we possess qualities other than fearlessness. We are patient and know the time is not yet right, the dangers of the daggermouths have not been overcome yet and until they have it would be prudent to wait.}}

==Trivia==
*Before the release of {{RSL|The Tale of the Muspah}} in ''{{RSL|RuneScape 3}}'', some players speculated the ritual site was on Acheron,{{CitePostbag|issue=9|letter=5|quote=Maybe it's the land of Acheron I have heard about.}} although with the release of the {{RSL|Ritual of the Mahjarrat}} this was disconfirmed.

